canonical:
  title: 山居
  author: 李仁老
  language: lzh
  text: 春去花猶在天晴谷自陰杜鵑啼白晝始覺卜居深
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 山居
  author: 李仁老
  language: lzh
  text: 春去花猶在。天晴谷自陰。杜鵑啼白晝。始覺卜居深。
korean:
  title: 산거
  author: 이인로
  language: kor
  text: |-
    봄은 가도 꽃은 아직 있는데
    하늘은 갰건만 골짜기는 절로 침침하네
    두견이 한낮에 우짖으니
    비로소 깨닫노라 깊은 골에 사는 줄을
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_010_0160&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Mountain Dwelling
  author: Lee In-ro
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Spring departs, yet blossoms remain.
    The sky clears, but the valley stays shadowed.
    The cuckoo cries in broad daylight—
    Only then do I perceive how deep my mountain refuge lies.
  footnotes:
    - The cuckoo (두견이) is traditionally associated in East Asian poetry with longing and the passage of seasons, here marking the speaker's recognition of their isolated dwelling.
